    <edge source="1. Regarding staffing numbers in schools, do you believe that there should be a specific target or range set for the number of staff members per student to support the health and education objectives of the plan?&#10;2. For improving the implementation of standards for healthy preschools, would you consider it appropriate to enforce those standards more strictly, and if so, what measures could be taken to ensure compliance?" target="1. To address the issue of children not meeting physical activity guidelines, Sport Wales, Public Health Wales, and Natural Resources Wales are currently working together as a collaborative to enhance the joint delivery of physical activity programs for children. They are specifically focusing on improving the efficiency of existing school programs, such as eco-schools, the Welsh network of healthy schools, and sports programs. The goal is to create better alignment and coordination among these initiatives to encourage increased physical activity among children in school settings.&#10;2. Increasing the number of physically active children can have numerous positive impacts on their lives, including better academic performance, improved mental health, and reduced risk of chronic diseases. To achieve this goal, it is essential to create a supportive environment that integrates physical activity into daily routines, makes it fun and accessible, and involves parents and teachers in promoting healthy habits. By prioritizing physical activity in primary education, schools can contribute significantly to shaping lifelong healthy behaviors among children.">
