    </edge>
    <edge source="1. Regarding staffing numbers in schools, do you believe that there should be a specific target or range set for the number of staff members per student to support the health and education objectives of the plan?&#10;2. For improving the implementation of standards for healthy preschools, would you consider it appropriate to enforce those standards more strictly, and if so, what measures could be taken to ensure compliance?" target="1. The strategy development board is currently open to considering the idea of setting specific targets or ranges for staff members per student to support health and education objectives in schools, but it has not been explicitly included in their plans so far. This could be addressed in the consultation response if raised specifically.&#10;2. To improve the implementation of standards for healthy preschools, Dr. Frank Atherton suggests tightening existing standards and enforcing them more strictly to ensure compliance. He believes that local school leaders should be responsible for ensuring compliance with physical activity guidelines in preschools under the new curriculum, which places obligations on them regarding what they do in their schools to promote healthy weight and well-being in children.">
