physical activity fun, accessible, and part of the daily routine. Research shows that children who are more physically active tend to have better academic performance, improved mental health, and reduced risk of chronic diseases. By prioritizing physical activity in primary education, schools can play a critical role in shaping healthy habits that last a lifetime.">
