sure proper focus and resources. Engaging with children and young people to inform anti-obesity strategies is also crucial. Developing targeted interventions for specific groups, such as teenage girls, can help address the decline in physical activity among them.&#10;4. Partnerships between schools and Public Health Wales could drive population-level approaches to physical activity. Improving the quality of food provided at schools and addressing hunger through national-level initiatives are also essential components of promoting healthier school environments.&#10;5. A second measurement in the Child Measurement Programme can provide a better understanding of the development of overweight and obesity in Welsh children, informing future strategies and interventions.">
