    <edge source="1. Implementing a commitment to embed physical activity at an early stage in primary school education would involve creating an environment that encourages and promotes regular movement and exercise throughout the day. This could include:&#10;* Integrating physical activity into daily classroom routines, such as active lessons or brain breaks&#10;* Providing adequate space and equipment for physical education classes and recess&#10;* Training teachers to incorporate movement into their teaching methods&#10;* Encouraging parental involvement in promoting physical activity outside of school hours. &#10;2. Increasing the number of children who meet the recommended physical activity guidelines can be achieved by creating a positive and supportive environment that makes physical activity fun, accessible, and part of the daily routine. Research shows that children who are more physically active tend to have better academic performance, improved mental health, and reduced risk of chronic diseases. By prioritizing physical activity in primary education, schools can play a critical role in shaping healthy habits that last a lifetime." target="1. To address the issue of children not meeting physical activity guidelines, Sport Wales, Public Health Wales, and Natural Resources Wales are currently working together as a collaborative to enhance the joint delivery of physical activity programs for children. They are specifically focusing on improving the efficiency of existing school programs, such as eco-schools, the Welsh network of healthy schools, and sports programs. The goal is to create better alignment and coordination among these initiatives to encourage increased physical activity among children in school settings.&#10;2. Increasing the number of physically active children can have numerous positive impacts on their lives, including better academic performance, improved mental health, and reduced risk of chronic diseases. To achieve this goal, it is essential to create a supportive environment that integrates physical activity into daily routines, makes it fun and accessible, and involves parents and teachers in promoting healthy habits. By prioritizing physical activity in primary education, schools can contribute significantly to shaping lifelong healthy behaviors among children.">
