d perhaps design and build them in a different way. So, on a personal basis, I would certainly support your view that we should be looking to use the sports environment in schools in the same way as we use leisure centres. There are all kinds of barriers in there, and I understand all of that, and it's not really my field, exactly as you say, but, as a matter of principle, I think it's a good one to pursue.&#10;Speaker: Dawn Bowden AM&#10;Content: Okay. Thank you. And widening it out to other public services buildings as well.&#10;Speaker: Dr Frank Atherton&#10;Content: Indeed.&#10;Speaker: Dawn Bowden AM&#10;Content: Yes. Okay. Thank you.&#10;Speaker: Lynne Neagle AM&#10;Content: Okay, thank you. We're going to move on now to talk about how we create healthy settings. I've got some questions from Suzy Davies.&#10;Speaker: Su">
