o addressing obesity prevention, as the government can divert and channel some of the £7 billion spent on health and social care towards broad prevention initiatives, including tackling being overweight and obesity in particular.&#10;&#10;In conclusion, although the revenue from the soft drink levy is smaller than anticipated, it should still be used to fund obesity prevention programs, given Dr. Frank Atherton's stance on hypothecation and the importance of considering the totality of resources going into public health programs.">
