ity and overweight issues in children. While there is currently no explicit mention of setting specific targets or ranges for staff members per student, the focus is on encouraging local leadership, implementing statutory guidance for physical education, engaging children and young people in anti-obesity strategies, developing targeted interventions for girls, forming partnerships between schools and Public Health Wales, improving the quality of school food, and examining the potential benefits of a second measurement in the Child Measurement Programme.&#10;&#10;Although increased investment will be required from the Welsh Government to support and fund initiatives aimed at tackling childhood obesity, it is crucial to assess the effectiveness of existing programs and seek ways to improve or optimize their impact before committing new resources. This approach will help ensure that investments are directed towards interventions with proven benefits and contribute to the overall goal of reducing childhood obesity in Wales.">
